#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:362
msgid "How to Maximize Your 401(k)"
msgstr "Cómo maximizar su 401(k)"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:369
msgid "Get the Full Employer Match"
msgstr "Obtenga la igualación completa del empleador"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:370
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Always contribute at least enough to get 100%% of your employer's matching "
"contribution. It's essentially free money!"
msgstr ""
"Contribuya siempre al menos lo suficiente para obtener el 100 % de la "
"contribución equivalente de su empleador. ¡Es esencialmente dinero gratis!"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:378
msgid "Increase Contributions Over Time"
msgstr "Aumentar las contribuciones con el tiempo"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:379
msgid ""
"Whenever you get a raise, consider putting at least half of it toward your "
"401(k). You won't miss money you never had."
msgstr ""
"Siempre que obtenga un aumento, considere destinar al menos la mitad a su "
"401(k). No extrañarás dinero que nunca tuviste."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:387
msgid "Use Catch-Up Contributions"
msgstr "Utilice contribuciones de actualización"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:388
msgid ""
"If you're 50 or older, take advantage of catch-up contributions to "
"accelerate your savings before retirement."
msgstr ""
"Si tiene 50 años o más, aproveche las contribuciones de recuperación para "
"acelerar sus ahorros antes de la jubilación."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:396
#, python-format
msgid "The 4%% Rule Explained"
msgstr "La regla del 4%% explicada"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:397
#, python-format
msgid ""
"The 4%% rule is a popular retirement withdrawal strategy. It suggests "
"withdrawing 4%% of your retirement savings in the first year, then adjusting"
" for inflation each year after."
msgstr ""
"La regla del 4%% es una estrategia popular de retiro para la jubilación. "
"Sugiere retirar el 4%% de sus ahorros para la jubilación durante el primer "
"año y luego ajustarlo a la inflación cada año posterior."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/401k_calculator.html:399
