#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:154
msgid "Compare Terms"
msgstr "Comparar términos"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:174
msgid "Payment Schedule (First 12 Months)"
msgstr "Calendario de pagos (primeros 12 meses)"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:200
msgid "Calculate Your Payment"
msgstr "Calcule su pago"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:201
msgid "Enter your loan details to see your monthly payment and schedule."
msgstr ""
"Ingrese los detalles de su préstamo para ver su pago mensual y su "
"cronograma."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:215
msgid "The total amount you plan to borrow."
msgstr "El monto total que planea pedir prestado."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:222
msgid "Enter the annual interest rate and repayment period."
msgstr "Ingrese la tasa de interés anual y el período de pago."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:229
msgid "See your payment and compare different terms."
msgstr "Vea su pago y compare diferentes términos."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:241
msgid "How is my monthly payment calculated?"
msgstr "¿Cómo se calcula mi pago mensual?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:247
msgid ""
"Monthly payments are calculated using the standard amortization formula: M ="
" P[r(1+r)^n]/[(1+r)^n-1], where P is principal, r is monthly rate, and n is "
"number of payments."
msgstr ""
"Los pagos mensuales se calculan utilizando la fórmula de amortización "
"estándar: M = P[r(1+r)^n]/[(1+r)^n-1], donde P es el capital, r es la tasa "
"mensual y n es el número de pagos."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:253
msgid "Should I choose a shorter or longer term?"
msgstr "¿Debo elegir un plazo más corto o más largo?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:259
msgid ""
"Shorter terms mean higher monthly payments but less total interest. Longer "
"terms lower your monthly payment but cost more over time. Choose based on "
"your budget and goals."
msgstr ""
"Plazos más cortos significan pagos mensuales más altos pero menos intereses "
"totales. Los plazos más largos reducen su pago mensual pero cuestan más con "
"el tiempo. Elija según su presupuesto y objetivos."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:265
msgid "What's the benefit of biweekly payments?"
msgstr "¿Cuál es el beneficio de los pagos quincenales?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/payment_calculator.html:271
msgid ""
"Paying half your monthly payment every two weeks results in 26 half-payments"
" (13 full payments) per year instead of 12. This extra payment goes to "
"principal, saving interest and time."
msgstr ""
"Pagar la mitad de su pago mensual cada dos semanas resulta en 26 medios "
"pagos (13 pagos completos) por año en lugar de 12. Este pago adicional se "
"destina al capital, lo que ahorra intereses y tiempo."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/pension_calculator.html:5
