#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:280
msgid "What is a Required Minimum Distribution?"
msgstr "¿Qué es una distribución mínima requerida?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:281
msgid ""
"A Required Minimum Distribution (RMD) is the minimum amount you must "
"withdraw from your retirement account each year once you reach a certain "
"age. The IRS requires these withdrawals to ensure you pay taxes on your tax-"
"deferred retirement savings."
msgstr ""
"Una distribución mínima requerida (RMD) es la cantidad mínima que debe "
"retirar de su cuenta de jubilación cada año una vez que alcance cierta edad."
" El IRS exige estos retiros para garantizar que usted pague impuestos sobre "
"sus ahorros para la jubilación con impuestos diferidos."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:287
msgid "Traditional IRAs require RMDs"
msgstr "Las IRA tradicionales requieren RMD"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:293
msgid "401(k) and 403(b) plans require RMDs"
msgstr "Los planes 401(k) y 403(b) requieren RMD"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:299
msgid "Roth IRAs do NOT require RMDs during your lifetime"
msgstr "Las IRA Roth NO requieren RMD durante su vida"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:306
msgid "RMD Penalties"
msgstr "Sanciones RMD"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:308
#, python-format
msgid "25%% Penalty for Missing RMDs"
msgstr "Penalización del 25%% por RMD faltantes"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:309
#, python-format
msgid ""
"If you don't take your full RMD by the deadline, you'll owe a 25%% excise "
"tax on the amount not withdrawn. This can be reduced to 10%% if corrected "
"promptly."
msgstr ""
"Si no retira su RMD completo antes de la fecha límite, deberá pagar un "
"impuesto especial del 25% sobre el monto no retirado. Esto se puede reducir "
"al 10%% si se corrige rápidamente."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:313
msgid "Deadline"
msgstr "Fecha límite"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:314
msgid ""
"RMDs must be taken by December 31st each year. First-year RMDs can be "
"delayed until April 1st of the following year (but you'll need to take two "
"RMDs that year)."
msgstr ""
"Los RMD deben tomarse antes del 31 de diciembre de cada año. Los RMD del "
"primer año se pueden retrasar hasta el 1 de abril del año siguiente (pero "
"deberás realizar dos RMD ese año)."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:326
msgid "How is my RMD calculated?"
msgstr "¿Cómo se calcula mi RMD?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:331
msgid ""
"Your RMD is calculated by dividing your prior year-end account balance by "
"your life expectancy factor from the IRS Uniform Lifetime Table. For "
"example, if your balance was $500,000 and your factor is 26.5, your RMD "
"would be $18,868."
msgstr ""
"Su RMD se calcula dividiendo el saldo de su cuenta de fin de año anterior "
"por su factor de esperanza de vida de la Tabla Uniforme de Vida del IRS. Por"
" ejemplo, si su saldo era de $500 000 y su factor es 26,5, su RMD sería de "
"$18 868."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:336
msgid "Can I withdraw more than my RMD?"
msgstr "¿Puedo retirar más que mi RMD?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:341
msgid ""
"Yes! The RMD is the minimum you must withdraw. You can always take more. "
"However, any excess cannot be applied to future years' RMDs. Extra "
"withdrawals will be taxed as ordinary income."
msgstr ""
"¡Sí! El RMD es el mínimo que debes retirar. Siempre puedes tomar más. Sin "
"embargo, ningún exceso no podrá aplicarse a los RMD de años futuros. Los "
"retiros adicionales tributarán como ingresos ordinarios."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:346
msgid "What if I have multiple IRAs?"
msgstr "¿Qué pasa si tengo varias cuentas IRA?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:351
msgid ""
"You must calculate RMDs separately for each Traditional IRA you own. "
"However, you can take the total amount from any one or combination of your "
"IRAs. 401(k) RMDs must be taken from each account separately."
msgstr ""
"Debe calcular los RMD por separado para cada IRA tradicional que posea. Sin "
"embargo, puede tomar el monto total de cualquiera o combinación de sus IRA. "
"Los RMD 401(k) deben tomarse de cada cuenta por separado."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:5
msgid "Roth IRA Calculator - Tax-Free Retirement Savings"
msgstr "Calculadora Roth IRA - Ahorros para la jubilación libres de impuestos"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:7
msgid ""
"Calculate your Roth IRA tax-free retirement savings. See projected balance, "
"income limits, and compare with Traditional IRA using our free calculator."
msgstr ""
"Calcule sus ahorros de jubilación libres de impuestos Roth IRA. Vea el saldo"
" proyectado, los límites de ingresos y compárelos con la IRA tradicional "
"usando nuestra calculadora gratuita."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:10
msgid ""
"Roth IRA calculator, Roth IRA contribution limits, tax-free retirement, Roth"
" vs Traditional IRA, retirement calculator"
msgstr ""
"Calculadora Roth IRA, límites de contribución de Roth IRA, jubilación libre "
"de impuestos, Roth vs IRA tradicional, calculadora de jubilación"

