msgstr "Contribuciones Roth IRA"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:134
msgid "Current Roth IRA Balance"
msgstr "Saldo actual de Roth IRA"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:171
msgid "Calculate Roth IRA"
msgstr "Calcular la cuenta IRA Roth"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:177
msgid "Roth IRA Key Benefit"
msgstr "Beneficio clave de Roth IRA"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:178
#, python-format
msgid ""
"All growth is 100%% tax-free! Pay taxes now on contributions, never pay "
"taxes on gains or withdrawals."
msgstr ""
"¡Todo el crecimiento es 100%% libre de impuestos! Pague impuestos ahora "
"sobre las aportaciones, nunca pague impuestos sobre las ganancias o los "
"retiros."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:193
msgid ""
"Fill out the form to see your projected Roth IRA tax-free balance at "
"retirement."
msgstr ""
"Complete el formulario para ver su saldo libre de impuestos de Roth IRA "
"proyectado al momento de la jubilación."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:199
msgid "Calculating your Roth IRA projection..."
msgstr "Calculando su proyección Roth IRA..."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:220
msgid "Tax-Free Balance at Retirement"
msgstr "Saldo libre de impuestos al momento de la jubilación"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:222
#, python-format
msgid "100%% yours - no taxes owed!"
msgstr "100%% tuyo: ¡sin adeudar impuestos!"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:227
msgid "Tax-Free Monthly Income"
msgstr "Ingreso Mensual Libre de Impuestos"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:240
msgid "Income Limit Affects Eligibility"
msgstr "El límite de ingresos afecta la elegibilidad"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:257
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:314
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:640
msgid "Tax-Free Gains"
msgstr "Ganancias libres de impuestos"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:261
msgid "Eligibility"
msgstr "Elegibilidad"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:268
msgid "Roth IRA vs Traditional IRA Comparison"
msgstr "Comparación de Roth IRA y IRA tradicional"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:271
msgid "Roth IRA (Tax-Free)"
msgstr "Roth IRA (libre de impuestos)"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:275
msgid "Traditional (After-Tax)"
msgstr "Tradicional (después de impuestos)"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:279
msgid "Roth Advantage"
msgstr "Ventaja Roth"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:283
msgid ""
"Comparison assumes Traditional IRA withdrawals are taxed at your expected "
"retirement tax rate."
msgstr ""
"La comparación supone que los retiros de cuentas IRA tradicionales se gravan"
" según la tasa impositiva de jubilación esperada."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:290
msgid "Roth IRA Growth"
msgstr "Crecimiento de la cuenta IRA Roth"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:298
msgid "Contributions vs Tax-Free Gains"
msgstr "Contribuciones versus ganancias libres de impuestos"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:331
msgid "Why Choose a Roth IRA?"
msgstr "¿Por qué elegir una cuenta IRA Roth?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:338
msgid "Tax-Free Withdrawals"
msgstr "Retiros libres de impuestos"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:339
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Qualified withdrawals in retirement are 100%% tax-free, including all "
"investment gains."
msgstr ""
"Los retiros calificados durante la jubilación son 100% libres de impuestos, "
"incluidas todas las ganancias de inversiones."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:347
msgid "No Required Minimum Distributions"
msgstr "No se requieren distribuciones mínimas"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:348
msgid ""
"Unlike Traditional IRAs, Roth IRAs have no RMDs during your lifetime, giving"
" you more control."
msgstr ""
"A diferencia de las IRA tradicionales, las IRA Roth no tienen RMD durante su"
" vida, lo que le brinda más control."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:356
msgid "Contribution Flexibility"
msgstr "Flexibilidad de contribución"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:357
msgid ""
"You can withdraw contributions (not earnings) at any time without penalties."
msgstr ""
"Puedes retirar aportaciones (no ganancias) en cualquier momento sin "
"penalizaciones."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:365
msgid "2024 Roth IRA Income Limits"
msgstr "Límites de ingresos de Roth IRA 2024"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:368
msgid "Single Filers"
msgstr "Declarantes solteros"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:371
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:388
msgid "Full contribution"
msgstr "Contribución completa"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:372
msgid "Under $146,000"
msgstr "Menos de $146,000"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:375
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:392
msgid "Reduced contribution"
msgstr "Contribución reducida"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:376
msgid "$146,000 - $161,000"
msgstr "$146,000 - $161,000"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:379
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:396
msgid "Not eligible"
msgstr "No elegible"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:380
msgid "Over $161,000"
msgstr "Más de $161,000"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:389
msgid "Under $230,000"
msgstr "Menos de $230,000"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:393
msgid "$230,000 - $240,000"
msgstr "$230,000 - $240,000"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:397
msgid "Over $240,000"
msgstr "Más de $240,000"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:411
msgid "What is the 5-year rule for Roth IRAs?"
msgstr "¿Cuál es la regla de los 5 años para las cuentas IRA Roth?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:416
msgid ""
"To withdraw earnings tax-free, your Roth IRA must be open for at least 5 "
"years AND you must be 59½ or older. Contributions can always be withdrawn "
"tax and penalty-free."
msgstr ""
"Para retirar ganancias libres de impuestos, su Roth IRA debe estar abierta "
"durante al menos 5 años Y usted debe tener 59 años y medio o más. Las "
"contribuciones siempre se pueden retirar libres de impuestos y multas."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:421
msgid "Can I have both a Roth and Traditional IRA?"
msgstr "¿Puedo tener una IRA Roth y una IRA tradicional?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:426
msgid ""
"Yes! You can contribute to both, but your combined contributions cannot "
"exceed the annual limit ($7,000 in 2024, or $8,000 if 50+). Many people "
"split contributions to diversify their tax exposure."
msgstr ""
"¡Sí! Puede contribuir a ambos, pero sus contribuciones combinadas no pueden "
"exceder el límite anual ($7,000 en 2024, o $8,000 si tiene 50 años o más). "
"Muchas personas dividen sus contribuciones para diversificar su exposición "
"fiscal."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:431
msgid "What is a Backdoor Roth IRA?"
msgstr "¿Qué es una cuenta IRA Roth de puerta trasera?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:436
msgid ""
"A Backdoor Roth is a strategy for high earners who exceed income limits. You"
" contribute to a Traditional IRA (non-deductible) and then convert it to a "
"Roth IRA. Consult a tax advisor as this has tax implications."
msgstr ""
"Un Backdoor Roth es una estrategia para personas con altos ingresos que "
"exceden los límites de ingresos. Usted contribuye a una IRA tradicional (no "
"deducible) y luego la convierte en una IRA Roth. Consulte a un asesor fiscal"
" ya que esto tiene implicaciones fiscales."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/roth_ira_calculator.html:597
msgid "Tax-Free Balance"
msgstr "Saldo libre de impuestos"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/salary_calculator.html:5
msgid "Salary Calculator - Convert Hourly, Monthly, Annual Pay"
msgstr "Calculadora de salario: conversión de salario por hora, mes y año"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/salary_calculator.html:7
#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/salary_calculator.html:62
msgid ""
"Convert your salary between hourly, weekly, monthly, and annual amounts. "
"Calculate raises, compare job offers, and compute overtime pay."
msgstr ""
"Convierta su salario entre montos por hora, semana, mes y año. Calcule "
"aumentos, compare ofertas de trabajo y calcule el pago de horas extras."

