#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/greatest_common_factor_calculator.html:202
msgid "Common Factors"
msgstr "Factores comunes"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:316
msgid "GCF Gauge"
msgstr "Indicador GCF"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:329
msgid "Common Factors Count"
msgstr "Los factores comunes cuentan"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:343
msgid "Factor Comparison"
msgstr "Comparación de factores"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:375
msgid "What is the Common Factor Calculator?"
msgstr "¿Qué es la Calculadora de Factor Común?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:377
msgid ""
"The Common Factor Calculator finds all factors that are common to two or "
"more numbers. It also calculates the Greatest Common Factor (GCF), which is "
"the largest number that divides all given numbers evenly."
msgstr ""
"La Calculadora de factores comunes encuentra todos los factores que son "
"comunes a dos o más números. También calcula el máximo común divisor (MCD), "
"que es el número más grande que divide todos los números dados en partes "
"iguales."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:380
msgid ""
"This calculator is useful for simplifying fractions, finding common "
"denominators, and solving mathematical problems involving multiple numbers."
msgstr ""
"Esta calculadora es útil para simplificar fracciones, encontrar "
"denominadores comunes y resolver problemas matemáticos que involucran varios"
" números."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:389
msgid "Click 'Calculate Common Factors' to find all common factors"
msgstr ""
"Haga clic en 'Calcular factores comunes' para encontrar todos los factores "
"comunes"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:390
msgid "View the Greatest Common Factor (GCF) in the main result card"
msgstr ""
"Ver el máximo común divisor (MCD) en la tarjeta de resultados principal"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:391
msgid "See all common factors displayed as tags"
msgstr "Ver todos los factores comunes mostrados como etiquetas"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:392
msgid "Review detailed results showing factors of each number"
msgstr ""
"Revise los resultados detallados que muestran los factores de cada número."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:393
msgid "Use charts to visualize factor relationships"
msgstr "Utilice gráficos para visualizar las relaciones entre factores."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:394
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:464
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:283
msgid "Follow the step-by-step solution to understand the process"
msgstr "Siga la solución paso a paso para comprender el proceso."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:405
msgid ""
"Numbers that divide evenly into all given numbers. For example, common "
"factors of 12 and 18 are 1, 2, 3, and 6."
msgstr ""
"Números que dividen uniformemente a todos los números dados. Por ejemplo, "
"los factores comunes de 12 y 18 son 1, 2, 3 y 6."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:411
msgid ""
"The largest number that divides all given numbers evenly. Also known as "
"Greatest Common Divisor (GCD)."
msgstr ""
"El número más grande que divide todos los números dados en partes iguales. "
"También conocido como máximo común divisor (MCD)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:415
msgid "Factor Comparison Chart"
msgstr "Cuadro de comparación de factores"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/common_factor_calculator.html:417
msgid ""
"Visual representation showing which factors belong to each number and which "
"are common to all."
msgstr ""
"Representación visual que muestra qué factores pertenecen a cada número y "
"cuáles son comunes a todos."

