msgstr "Calcular distancia"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:351
#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/fuel_cost_calculator.html:82
#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/fuel_cost_calculator.html:444
#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/speed_calculator.html:52
#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/speed_calculator.html:109
#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/speed_calculator.html:151
msgid "Calculate Distance"
msgstr "Calcular distancia"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:396
msgid ""
"Enter coordinates for two points to calculate the distance between them."
msgstr ""
"Ingrese las coordenadas de dos puntos para calcular la distancia entre "
"ellos."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:453
msgid "What is a Distance Calculator?"
msgstr "¿Qué es una calculadora de distancia?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:455
msgid ""
"A distance calculator computes the distance between two points in various "
"coordinate systems and using different distance metrics. It supports 2D and "
"3D Euclidean distance, Manhattan distance, geographic distance, and "
"Minkowski distance."
msgstr ""
"Una calculadora de distancia calcula la distancia entre dos puntos en varios"
" sistemas de coordenadas y utilizando diferentes métricas de distancia. "
"Admite distancia euclidiana 2D y 3D, distancia de Manhattan, distancia "
"geográfica y distancia de Minkowski."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:463
msgid "Select the distance type from the dropdown menu"
msgstr "Seleccione el tipo de distancia en el menú desplegable"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:464
msgid ""
"Enter the coordinates for point 1 and point 2 based on the selected type"
msgstr ""
"Ingrese las coordenadas para el punto 1 y el punto 2 según el tipo "
"seleccionado"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:465
msgid "For geographic distance, enter latitude and longitude in degrees"
msgstr ""
"Para la distancia geográfica, ingrese la latitud y la longitud en grados."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:466
msgid ""
"For Minkowski distance, enter comma-separated coordinates and the p value"
msgstr ""
"Para la distancia de Minkowski, ingrese las coordenadas separadas por comas "
"y el valor p"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:467
msgid "Click Calculate to get the distance with step-by-step solution"
msgstr ""
"Haga clic en Calcular para obtener la distancia con la solución paso a paso"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:468
msgid "Review the results, visualization, and detailed explanation"
msgstr "Revise los resultados, la visualización y la explicación detallada."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:474
msgid "Understanding Distance Types"
msgstr "Comprender los tipos de distancia"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:477
msgid "Euclidean Distance"
msgstr "Distancia euclidiana"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:479
msgid ""
"The straight-line distance between two points. In 2D: √((x₂-x₁)² + (y₂-"
"y₁)²). Represents the shortest path."
msgstr ""
"La distancia en línea recta entre dos puntos. En 2D: √((x₂-x₁)² + (y₂-y₁)²)."
" Representa el camino más corto."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:483
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:738
msgid "Manhattan Distance"
msgstr "Distancia de Manhattan"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:485
msgid ""
"The sum of absolute differences: |x₂-x₁| + |y₂-y₁|. Also called taxicab "
"distance, representing distance along grid lines."
msgstr ""
"La suma de diferencias absolutas: |x₂-x₁| + |y₂-y₁|. También llamada "
"distancia de taxi, que representa la distancia a lo largo de las líneas de "
"la cuadrícula."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:489
msgid "Geographic Distance"
msgstr "Distancia geográfica"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:491
msgid ""
"Uses the Haversine formula to calculate great-circle distance between two "
"points on Earth using latitude and longitude."
msgstr ""
"Utiliza la fórmula de Haversine para calcular la distancia del círculo "
"máximo entre dos puntos de la Tierra utilizando la latitud y la longitud."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:497
msgid ""
"A generalized distance metric. p=1 gives Manhattan, p=2 gives Euclidean, p=∞"
" gives Chebyshev distance."
msgstr ""
"Una métrica de distancia generalizada. p=1 da Manhattan, p=2 da euclidiana, "
"p=∞ da la distancia de Chebyshev."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:508
msgid "Example 1: 2D Euclidean Distance"
msgstr "Ejemplo 1: Distancia euclidiana 2D"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:509
msgid "Point 1: (0, 0), Point 2: (3, 4)"
msgstr "Punto 1: (0, 0), Punto 2: (3, 4)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:510
msgid "Distance: 5.0"
msgstr "Distancia: 5.0"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:513
msgid "Example 2: Geographic Distance"
msgstr "Ejemplo 2: Distancia geográfica"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:514
msgid "New York: (40.7128°N, 74.0060°W), London: (51.5074°N, 0.1278°W)"
msgstr "Nueva York: (40,7128°N, 74,0060°W), Londres: (51,5074°N, 0,1278°W)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:515
msgid "Distance: ~5,585 km"
msgstr "Distancia: ~5.585 kilómetros"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:528
msgid ""
"For geographic distance, latitude must be between -90° and 90°, longitude "
"between -180° and 180°."
msgstr ""
"Para la distancia geográfica, la latitud debe estar entre -90° y 90°, la "
"longitud entre -180° y 180°."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:534
msgid ""
"For Minkowski distance, both points must have the same number of dimensions."
msgstr ""
"Para la distancia de Minkowski, ambos puntos deben tener el mismo número de "
"dimensiones."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:540
msgid ""
"Euclidean distance is always less than or equal to Manhattan distance for "
"the same points."
msgstr ""
"La distancia euclidiana es siempre menor o igual a la distancia de Manhattan"
" para los mismos puntos."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:801
msgid "Distance Visualization"
msgstr "Visualización de distancia"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:4
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:21
msgid "Exponent Calculator - Calculate Powers & Roots"
msgstr "Calculadora de exponentes: calcular potencias y raíces"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:5
msgid ""
"Free exponent calculator to calculate exponents, powers, square roots, cube "
"roots, and nth roots. Calculate positive, negative, and fractional exponents"
" with step-by-step solutions. Perfect for algebra and math homework."
msgstr ""
"Calculadora de exponentes gratuita para calcular exponentes, potencias, "
"raíces cuadradas, raíces cúbicas y raíces enésimas. Calcula exponentes "
"positivos, negativos y fraccionarios con soluciones paso a paso. Perfecto "
"para tareas de álgebra y matemáticas."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:6
msgid ""
"exponent calculator, power calculator, calculate exponent, calculate power, "
"square root calculator, cube root calculator, nth root calculator, "
"exponentiation calculator, how to calculate exponents, scientific notation "
"calculator, root calculator, math calculator, power finder"
msgstr ""
"calculadora de exponentes, calculadora de potencia, calcular exponente, "
"calcular potencia, calculadora de raíz cuadrada, calculadora de raíz cúbica,"
" calculadora de raíz enésima, calculadora de exponenciación, cómo calcular "
"exponentes, calculadora de notación científica, calculadora de raíz, "
"calculadora matemática, buscador de potencia"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:22
msgid ""
"Free exponent calculator to calculate exponents, powers, square roots, cube "
"roots, and nth roots. Calculate positive, negative, and fractional exponents"
" with step-by-step solutions."
msgstr ""
"Calculadora de exponentes gratuita para calcular exponentes, potencias, "
"raíces cuadradas, raíces cúbicas y raíces enésimas. Calcula exponentes "
"positivos, negativos y fraccionarios con soluciones paso a paso."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:32
msgid "Professional Exponent Calculator - Free Online Tool"
msgstr "Calculadora de exponentes profesional: herramienta gratuita en línea"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:33
msgid ""
"Calculate exponents, powers, and roots. Free online calculator with step-by-"
"step solutions and visualizations."
msgstr ""
"Calcular exponentes, potencias y raíces. Calculadora online gratuita con "
"soluciones y visualizaciones paso a paso."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:46
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:169
msgid "Professional Exponent Calculator"
msgstr "Calculadora de exponentes profesional"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:59
msgid ""
"Free online exponent calculator. Calculate powers, roots, and "
"exponentiations with step-by-step solutions and visualizations."
msgstr ""
"Calculadora de exponentes online gratuita. Calcule potencias, raíces y "
"exponenciaciones con soluciones y visualizaciones paso a paso."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:66
msgid "Calculate exponents and powers"
msgstr "Calcular exponentes y potencias."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:67
msgid "Calculate square roots"
msgstr "Calcular raíces cuadradas"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:68
msgid "Calculate cube roots"
msgstr "Calcular raíces cúbicas"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:69
msgid "Calculate nth roots"
msgstr "Calcular raíces enésimas"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:70
msgid "Support for negative and fractional exponents"
msgstr "Soporte para exponentes negativos y fraccionarios."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:80
msgid "How to Use Exponent Calculator"
msgstr "Cómo utilizar la calculadora de exponentes"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:81
msgid "Step-by-step guide on calculating exponents and roots"
msgstr "Guía paso a paso para calcular exponentes y raíces"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:86
msgid "Choose between Exponent (power) or Root calculation"
msgstr "Elija entre cálculo de exponente (potencia) o raíz"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:90
#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/bandwidth_calculator.html:106
msgid "Enter Values"
msgstr "Introducir valores"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:91
msgid ""
"Enter the base and exponent (for power) or base and root index (for root)"
msgstr ""
"Ingrese la base y el exponente (para potencia) o el índice base y raíz (para"
" raíz)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:96
msgid ""
"Click Calculate to get the result with step-by-step solution and "
"visualization"
msgstr ""
"Haga clic en Calcular para obtener el resultado con la solución y "
"visualización paso a paso."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:101
msgid ""
"Review the calculated result, scientific notation, and detailed explanation"
msgstr ""
"Revise el resultado calculado, la notación científica y la explicación "
"detallada."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:114
msgid "What is an exponent?"
msgstr "¿Qué es un exponente?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:117
msgid ""
"An exponent (or power) indicates how many times a number (base) is "
"multiplied by itself. For example, 2³ means 2 × 2 × 2 = 8."
msgstr ""
"Un exponente (o potencia) indica cuántas veces se multiplica un número "
"(base) por sí mismo. Por ejemplo, 2³ significa 2 × 2 × 2 = 8."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:122
msgid "What is a negative exponent?"
msgstr "¿Qué es un exponente negativo?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:125
msgid ""
"A negative exponent means taking the reciprocal. For example, 2⁻³ = 1/(2³) ="
" 1/8 = 0.125."
msgstr ""
"Un exponente negativo significa tomar el recíproco. Por ejemplo, 2⁻³ = "
"1/(2³) = 1/8 = 0,125."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:130
msgid "What is a fractional exponent?"
msgstr "¿Qué es un exponente fraccionario?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:133
msgid ""
"A fractional exponent represents a root. For example, 8^(1/3) = ∛8 = 2, "
"which is the cube root of 8."
msgstr ""
"Un exponente fraccionario representa una raíz. Por ejemplo, 8^(1/3) = ∛8 = "
"2, que es la raíz cúbica de 8."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:138
msgid "What is the square root?"
msgstr "¿Qué es la raíz cuadrada?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:141
msgid ""
"The square root of a number is a value that, when multiplied by itself, "
"gives the original number. For example, √16 = 4 because 4 × 4 = 16."
msgstr ""
"La raíz cuadrada de un número es un valor que multiplicado por sí mismo da "
"el número original. Por ejemplo, √16 = 4 porque 4 × 4 = 16."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:146
msgid "Can I calculate roots of negative numbers?"
msgstr "¿Puedo calcular raíces de números negativos?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:149
msgid ""
"Odd roots (like cube root) of negative numbers are real numbers. Even roots "
"(like square root) of negative numbers are not real numbers (they are "
"complex)."
msgstr ""
"Las raíces impares (como la raíz cúbica) de números negativos son números "
"reales. Incluso las raíces (como la raíz cuadrada) de números negativos no "
"son números reales (son complejas)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:172
msgid ""
"Calculate exponents, powers, square roots, cube roots, and nth roots. "
"Supports positive, negative, and fractional exponents."
msgstr ""
"Calcula exponentes, potencias, raíces cuadradas, raíces cúbicas y raíces "
"enésimas. Admite exponentes positivos, negativos y fraccionarios."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:200
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:222
msgid "Exponent"
msgstr "Exponente"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:203
msgid "Root"
msgstr "Raíz"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:222
msgid "power"
msgstr "fuerza"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:227
msgid "Can be positive, negative, or fractional"
msgstr "Puede ser positivo, negativo o fraccionario."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:244
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/root_calculator.html:88
msgid "Root Index"
msgstr "Índice raíz"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:244
msgid "n for nth root"
msgstr "n para raíz enésima"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:249
msgid "2 = square root, 3 = cube root, etc."
msgstr "2 = raíz cuadrada, 3 = raíz cúbica, etc."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:260
msgid "Calculate exponent or root"
msgstr "Calcular exponente o raíz"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:308
msgid ""
"Enter base and exponent to calculate powers, or base and root index to "
"calculate roots."
msgstr ""
"Ingrese la base y el exponente para calcular potencias, o el índice de base "
"y raíz para calcular raíces."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:365
msgid "What is an Exponent Calculator?"
msgstr "¿Qué es una calculadora de exponentes?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:367
msgid ""
"An exponent calculator computes the result of raising a base number to a "
"power (exponent). It also calculates roots, which are the inverse operation "
"of exponentiation."
msgstr ""
"Una calculadora de exponentes calcula el resultado de elevar un número base "
"a una potencia (exponente). También calcula raíces, que son la operación "
"inversa de la exponenciación."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:370
msgid ""
"This calculator supports positive, negative, and fractional exponents, as "
"well as various types of roots including square roots, cube roots, and nth "
"roots."
msgstr ""
"Esta calculadora admite exponentes positivos, negativos y fraccionarios, así"
" como varios tipos de raíces, incluidas raíces cuadradas, raíces cúbicas y "
"raíces enésimas."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:378
msgid "Select calculation type: Exponent (power) or Root"
msgstr "Seleccione el tipo de cálculo: Exponente (potencia) o Raíz"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:379
msgid ""
"For exponent: Enter base and exponent (can be positive, negative, or "
"fractional)"
msgstr ""
"Para exponente: ingrese la base y el exponente (puede ser positivo, negativo"
" o fraccionario)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:380
msgid ""
"For root: Enter base and root index (2 for square root, 3 for cube root, "
"etc.)"
msgstr ""
"Para raíz: ingrese la base y el índice de raíz (2 para raíz cuadrada, 3 para"
" raíz cúbica, etc.)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:381
msgid "Click Calculate to get the result with step-by-step solution"
msgstr ""
"Haga clic en Calcular para obtener el resultado con la solución paso a paso"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:382
msgid ""
"Review the result, scientific notation, visualization, and detailed "
"explanation"
msgstr ""
"Revisar el resultado, notación científica, visualización y explicación "
"detallada."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:388
msgid "Understanding Exponents and Roots"
msgstr "Comprender los exponentes y las raíces"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:391
msgid "Positive Exponents"
msgstr "Exponentes positivos"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:393
msgid ""
"A positive exponent means multiplying the base by itself that many times. "
"Example: 2³ = 2 × 2 × 2 = 8."
msgstr ""
"Un exponente positivo significa multiplicar la base por sí misma tantas "
"veces. Ejemplo: 2³ = 2 × 2 × 2 = 8."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:397
msgid "Negative Exponents"
msgstr "Exponentes negativos"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:399
msgid ""
"A negative exponent means taking the reciprocal. Example: 2⁻³ = 1/(2³) = 1/8"
" = 0.125."
msgstr ""
"Un exponente negativo significa tomar el recíproco. Ejemplo: 2⁻³ = 1/(2³) = "
"1/8 = 0,125."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:403
msgid "Fractional Exponents"
msgstr "Exponentes fraccionarios"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:405
msgid ""
"A fractional exponent represents a root. Example: 8^(1/3) = ∛8 = 2 (cube "
"root of 8)."
msgstr ""
"Un exponente fraccionario representa una raíz. Ejemplo: 8^(1/3) = ∛8 = 2 "
"(raíz cúbica de 8)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:409
msgid "Roots"
msgstr "Raíces"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:411
msgid ""
"A root is the inverse of exponentiation. Square root (√) is the 2nd root, "
"cube root (∛) is the 3rd root, etc."
msgstr ""
"Una raíz es la inversa de la exponenciación. La raíz cuadrada (√) es la "
"segunda raíz, la raíz cúbica (∛) es la tercera raíz, etc."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:422
msgid "Example 1: Positive Exponent"
msgstr "Ejemplo 1: exponente positivo"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:423
msgid "Base: 2, Exponent: 3"
msgstr "Base: 2, Exponente: 3"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:424
msgid "Result: 2³ = 8"
msgstr "Resultado: 2³ = 8"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:427
msgid "Example 2: Negative Exponent"
msgstr "Ejemplo 2: exponente negativo"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:428
msgid "Base: 2, Exponent: -3"
msgstr "Base: 2, Exponente: -3"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:429
msgid "Result: 2⁻³ = 0.125"
msgstr "Resultado: 2⁻³ = 0,125"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:432
msgid "Example 3: Square Root"
msgstr "Ejemplo 3: raíz cuadrada"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:433
msgid "Base: 16, Root Index: 2"
msgstr "Base: 16, Índice raíz: 2"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:434
msgid "Result: √16 = 4"
msgstr "Resultado: √16 = 4"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:437
msgid "Example 4: Cube Root"
msgstr "Ejemplo 4: raíz cúbica"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:438
msgid "Base: 8, Root Index: 3"
msgstr "Base: 8, Índice raíz: 3"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:439
msgid "Result: ∛8 = 2"
msgstr "Resultado: ∛8 = 2"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:452
msgid "Zero raised to a negative power is undefined."
msgstr "El cero elevado a una potencia negativa no está definido."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:458
msgid ""
"Even roots of negative numbers are not real numbers (they are complex)."
msgstr ""
"Incluso las raíces de números negativos no son números reales (son "
"complejas)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:464
msgid "Odd roots of negative numbers are real numbers (e.g., ∛(-8) = -2)."
msgstr ""
"Las raíces impares de números negativos son números reales (por ejemplo, "
"∛(-8) = -2)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:470
msgid ""
"Very large exponents may result in overflow (result too large to represent)."
msgstr ""
"Los exponentes muy grandes pueden provocar un desbordamiento (el resultado "
"es demasiado grande para representarlo)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:710
msgid "Exponential Function Visualization"
msgstr "Visualización de funciones exponenciales"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/exponent_calculator.html:721
msgid "Root Visualization"
msgstr "Visualización de raíces"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:4
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:21
msgid "Factor Calculator - Find All Factors & Prime Factorization"
msgstr ""
"Calculadora de factores: encuentre todos los factores y factorización prima"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:5
msgid ""
"Free factor calculator to find all factors of a number, check if it's prime,"
" and get prime factorization. Calculate factors with step-by-step solutions "
"and visualizations. Perfect for number theory and math homework."
msgstr ""
"Calculadora de factores gratuita para encontrar todos los factores de un "
"número, comprobar si es primo y obtener la factorización prima. Calcula "
"factores con soluciones y visualizaciones paso a paso. Perfecto para teoría "
"de números y tareas de matemáticas."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:6
msgid ""
"factor calculator, find factors, prime factorization calculator, factors "
"finder, divisor calculator, prime number checker, factor finder, all factors"
" calculator, how to find factors, number factors calculator, math "
"calculator, factor solver"
msgstr ""
"calculadora de factores, encontrar factores, calculadora de factorización "
"prima, buscador de factores, calculadora de divisores, verificador de "
"números primos, buscador de factores, calculadora de todos los factores, "
"cómo encontrar factores, calculadora de factores numéricos, calculadora "
"matemática, solucionador de factores"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:22
msgid ""
"Free online factor calculator. Find all factors of a number, check if it's "
"prime, and get prime factorization with step-by-step solutions."
msgstr ""
"Calculadora de factores online gratuita. Encuentre todos los factores de un "
"número, verifique si es primo y obtenga la factorización prima con "
"soluciones paso a paso."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:32
msgid "Professional Factor Calculator - Free Online Tool"
msgstr "Calculadora de factores profesional: herramienta gratuita en línea"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:33
msgid ""
"Find all factors of a number, check if it's prime, and get prime "
"factorization. Free online calculator with step-by-step solutions."
msgstr ""
"Encuentre todos los factores de un número, verifique si es primo y obtenga "
"la factorización prima. Calculadora online gratuita con soluciones paso a "
"paso."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:46
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:169
msgid "Professional Factor Calculator"
msgstr "Calculadora de factores profesional"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:59
msgid ""
"Free online factor calculator. Find all factors of a number, check if it's "
"prime, and get prime factorization with step-by-step solutions and "
"visualizations."
msgstr ""
"Calculadora de factores online gratuita. Encuentre todos los factores de un "
"número, verifique si es primo y obtenga la factorización prima con "
"soluciones y visualizaciones paso a paso."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:66
msgid "Find all factors"
msgstr "Encuentra todos los factores"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:67
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/least_common_multiple_calculator.html:32
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:32
msgid "Prime factorization"
msgstr "factorización prima"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:68
msgid "Prime number checker"
msgstr "comprobador de números primos"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:80
msgid "How to Use Factor Calculator"
msgstr "Cómo utilizar la calculadora de factores"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:81
msgid "Step-by-step guide on finding factors and prime factorization"
msgstr "Guía paso a paso sobre cómo encontrar factores y factorización prima"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:85
msgid "Enter Number"
msgstr "Ingrese el número"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:86
msgid "Enter a positive integer to find its factors"
msgstr "Ingresa un número entero positivo para encontrar sus factores."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:91
msgid ""
"Click Calculate Factors to find all factors, check if prime, and get prime "
"factorization"
msgstr ""
"Haga clic en Calcular factores para encontrar todos los factores, verificar "
"si son primos y obtener la factorización prima."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:96
msgid ""
"Review all factors, prime factorization, prime status, and step-by-step "
"solution"
msgstr ""
"Revise todos los factores, factorización prima, estado primo y solución paso"
" a paso"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:101
msgid ""
"Use the visualization charts to understand factor distribution and prime "
"factors"
msgstr ""
"Utilice los gráficos de visualización para comprender la distribución de "
"factores y los factores primos."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:114
msgid "What is a factor?"
msgstr "¿Qué es un factor?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:117
msgid ""
"A factor is a number that divides evenly into another number. For example, "
"factors of 12 are 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, and 12."
msgstr ""
"Un factor es un número que se divide uniformemente entre otro número. Por "
"ejemplo, los factores de 12 son 1, 2, 3, 4, 6 y 12."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:122
msgid "What is prime factorization?"
msgstr "¿Qué es la factorización prima?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:125
msgid ""
"Prime factorization is expressing a number as a product of prime numbers. "
"For example, 12 = 2² × 3."
msgstr ""
"La factorización prima consiste en expresar un número como producto de "
"números primos. Por ejemplo, 12 = 2² × 3."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:130
msgid "What is a prime number?"
msgstr "¿Qué es un número primo?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:133
msgid ""
"A prime number is a number greater than 1 that has exactly two factors: 1 "
"and itself. Examples: 2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13."
msgstr ""
"Un número primo es un número mayor que 1 que tiene exactamente dos factores:"
" 1 y él mismo. Ejemplos: 2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:138
msgid "What is the difference between factors and proper factors?"
msgstr "¿Cuál es la diferencia entre factores y factores propios?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:141
msgid ""
"All factors include 1 and the number itself. Proper factors exclude the "
"number itself. For example, proper factors of 12 are 1, 2, 3, 4, and 6 "
"(excluding 12)."
msgstr ""
"Todos los factores incluyen 1 y el número mismo. Los factores propios "
"excluyen el número en sí. Por ejemplo, los factores propios de 12 son 1, 2, "
"3, 4 y 6 (excluyendo 12)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:146
msgid "Can I find factors of very large numbers?"
msgstr "¿Puedo encontrar factores de números muy grandes?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:149
msgid ""
"This calculator can handle numbers up to 10,000,000,000. For larger numbers,"
" factorization may take longer or may not be feasible."
msgstr ""
"Esta calculadora puede manejar números hasta 10.000.000.000. Para números "
"más grandes, la factorización puede llevar más tiempo o no ser factible."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:172
msgid ""
"Find all factors of a number, check if it's prime, and get prime "
"factorization with step-by-step solutions and visualizations."
msgstr ""
"Encuentre todos los factores de un número, verifique si es primo y obtenga "
"la factorización prima con soluciones y visualizaciones paso a paso."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:198
msgid "positive integer"
msgstr "entero positivo"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:210
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:458
msgid "Enter a positive integer (1 to 10,000,000,000)"
msgstr "Introduzca un número entero positivo (de 1 a 10.000.000.000)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:222
msgid "Calculate factors"
msgstr "Calcular factores"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:226
msgid "Calculate Factors"
msgstr "Calcular factores"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:280
msgid ""
"Enter a positive integer to find all its factors, check if it's prime, and "
"get prime factorization."
msgstr ""
"Ingrese un número entero positivo para encontrar todos sus factores, "
"verifique si es primo y obtenga la factorización prima."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/factor_calculator.html:290
