msgid "Function Curve"
msgstr "Curva de función"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/log_calculator.html:291
msgid "What is a Logarithm?"
msgstr "¿Qué es un logaritmo?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/log_calculator.html:293
msgid ""
"A logarithm is the inverse operation of exponentiation. If b^y = x, then "
"log_b(x) = y. The logarithm tells you what power you need to raise the base "
"to get the number."
msgstr ""
"Un logaritmo es la operación inversa de la exponenciación. Si b^y = x, "
"entonces log_b(x) = y. El logaritmo te dice qué potencia necesitas para "
"elevar la base para obtener el número."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/log_calculator.html:296
msgid ""
"Common logarithms: log₁₀ (base 10) and ln (natural log, base e ≈ 2.71828)."
msgstr ""
"Logaritmos comunes: log₁₀ (base 10) y ln (log natural, base e ≈ 2,71828)."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/log_calculator.html:303
msgid "Calculate log_b(x) - the power to which base b must be raised to get x"
msgstr ""
"Calcule log_b(x): la potencia a la que se debe elevar la base b para obtener"
" x"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/log_calculator.html:304
msgid "Calculate b^x - raise base b to the power x (inverse of logarithm)"
msgstr ""
"Calcular b^x - elevar la base b a la potencia x (inversa del logaritmo)"

