#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:291
msgid "Distribution"
msgstr "Distribución"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:322
msgid "What is a P-Value?"
msgstr "¿Qué es un valor P?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:324
msgid ""
"The p-value is the probability of observing a test statistic as extreme as, "
"or more extreme than, the observed value under the null hypothesis. It helps"
" determine statistical significance."
msgstr ""
"El valor p es la probabilidad de observar un estadístico de prueba tan "
"extremo o más extremo que el valor observado bajo la hipótesis nula. Ayuda a"
" determinar la significancia estadística."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:327
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Common significance levels: α = 0.05 (5%%), α = 0.01 (1%%), α = 0.10 (10%%)"
msgstr ""
"Niveles de significancia común: α = 0,05 (5%%), α = 0,01 (1%%), α = 0,10 "
"(10%%)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:332
msgid "Test Types"
msgstr "Tipos de prueba"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:334
msgid "Used when population standard deviation is known"
msgstr "Se utiliza cuando se conoce la desviación estándar de la población."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:335
msgid ""
"Used when population standard deviation is unknown (requires degrees of "
"freedom)"
msgstr ""
"Se utiliza cuando se desconoce la desviación estándar de la población "
"(requiere grados de libertad)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:336
msgid "Used for testing independence or goodness of fit"
msgstr "Se utiliza para probar la independencia o la bondad de ajuste."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:337
msgid "Used for comparing variances or in ANOVA"
msgstr "Se utiliza para comparar varianzas o en ANOVA."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:342
msgid "Interpreting P-Values"
msgstr "Interpretación de los valores P"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:344
msgid "Very strong evidence against null hypothesis"
msgstr "Evidencia muy fuerte contra la hipótesis nula."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:345
msgid "Strong evidence against null hypothesis (statistically significant)"
msgstr ""
"Evidencia sólida contra la hipótesis nula (estadísticamente significativa)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:346
msgid "Weak evidence against null hypothesis"
msgstr "Evidencia débil contra la hipótesis nula"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:347
msgid "Little to no evidence against null hypothesis"
msgstr "Poca o ninguna evidencia contra la hipótesis nula"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:355
msgid "Example 1: Z-Test"
msgstr "Ejemplo 1: prueba Z"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:361
msgid "Example 2: T-Test"
msgstr "Ejemplo 2: prueba T"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/p_value_calculator.html:363
msgid "Degrees of Freedom"
msgstr "Grados de libertad"

