msgid ""
"Enter a positive integer to find its prime factorization, prime factors, and"
" all factors."
msgstr ""
"Ingrese un número entero positivo para encontrar su factorización prima, "
"factores primos y todos los factores."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:212
msgid "Prime Factors Exponents"
msgstr "Exponentes de factores primos"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:257
msgid "What is Prime Factorization?"
msgstr "¿Qué es la factorización prima?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:259
msgid ""
"Prime factorization is the process of expressing a number as a product of "
"its prime factors. Every composite number can be uniquely expressed as a "
"product of prime numbers."
msgstr ""
"La factorización prima es el proceso de expresar un número como producto de "
"sus factores primos. Todo número compuesto se puede expresar de forma única "
"como producto de números primos."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:262
msgid "Example: 12 = 2² × 3 (2 × 2 × 3)"
msgstr "Ejemplo: 12 = 2² × 3 (2 × 2 × 3)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:269
msgid ""
"A number greater than 1 that has no positive divisors other than 1 and "
"itself"
msgstr ""
"Un número mayor que 1 que no tiene divisores positivos distintos de 1 y él "
"mismo."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:270
msgid "Prime Factor"
msgstr "factor primo"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:270
msgid "A prime number that divides the given number"
msgstr "Un número primo que divide al número dado."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:271
msgid "The unique representation of a number as a product of prime factors"
msgstr ""
"La representación única de un número como producto de factores primos."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:272
msgid "A number that divides the given number without a remainder"
msgstr "Un número que divide el número dado sin resto."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:279
msgid "Enter a positive integer"
msgstr "Introduzca un número entero positivo"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:280
msgid "Click 'Calculate' to find prime factorization"
msgstr "Haga clic en 'Calcular' para encontrar la factorización prima"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:281
msgid "Review prime factors and prime factorization"
msgstr "Revisar los factores primos y la factorización prima."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/prime_factorization_calculator.html:282
msgid "View all factors of the number"
msgstr "Ver todos los factores del número"

