msgid "%%"
msgstr "%%"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:191
#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:258
msgid "Voltage Drop (Volts)"
msgstr "Caída de voltaje (voltios)"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:343
msgid "What is Voltage Drop?"
msgstr "¿Qué es la caída de voltaje?"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:344
msgid ""
"Voltage drop is the reduction in voltage in an electrical circuit due to the"
" resistance of the conductors. It's important to keep voltage drop within "
"acceptable limits to ensure proper equipment operation."
msgstr ""
"La caída de voltaje es la reducción de voltaje en un circuito eléctrico "
"debido a la resistencia de los conductores. Es importante mantener la caída "
"de voltaje dentro de límites aceptables para garantizar el funcionamiento "
"adecuado del equipo."

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:351
msgid "Enter circuit parameters"
msgstr "Ingrese los parámetros del circuito"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:352
msgid "Select wire size and material"
msgstr "Seleccione el tamaño y el material del cable"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:358
msgid "Circuit Types"
msgstr "Tipos de circuito"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:360
msgid "Direct current circuits"
msgstr "Circuitos de corriente continua"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:361
msgid "Standard residential AC power"
msgstr "Alimentación de CA residencial estándar"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:362
msgid "Commercial and industrial power"
msgstr "Energía comercial e industrial."

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:367
msgid "Wire Materials"
msgstr "Materiales de alambre"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:369
msgid "Lower resistance, higher cost"
msgstr "Menor resistencia, mayor costo"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:370
msgid "Higher resistance, lower cost"
msgstr "Mayor resistencia, menor costo"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:377
msgid "DC Voltage Drop"
msgstr "Caída de voltaje CC"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:389
msgid "Acceptable Voltage Drop"
msgstr "Caída de voltaje aceptable"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:391
msgid "NEC recommends:"
msgstr "NEC recomienda:"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:392
#, python-format
msgid "• 3%% for branch circuits"
msgstr "• 3%% para circuitos derivados"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:393
#, python-format
msgid "• 5%% for combined feeder and branch circuits"
msgstr "• 5%% para circuitos combinados alimentadores y derivados"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:394
msgid "• Lower is better for sensitive equipment"
msgstr "• Más bajo es mejor para equipos sensibles"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:400
msgid ""
"Power factor is the ratio of real power to apparent power. For resistive "
"loads (heaters, incandescent lights), power factor is 1.0. For inductive "
"loads (motors, transformers), power factor is typically 0.7-0.9."
msgstr ""
"El factor de potencia es la relación entre la potencia real y la potencia "
"aparente. Para cargas resistivas (calentadores, luces incandescentes), el "
"factor de potencia es 1,0. Para cargas inductivas (motores, "
"transformadores), el factor de potencia suele ser de 0,7 a 0,9."

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:406
msgid "Voltage drop increases with wire length"
msgstr "La caída de voltaje aumenta con la longitud del cable"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:407
msgid "Larger wire sizes reduce voltage drop"
msgstr "Los tamaños de cables más grandes reducen la caída de voltaje"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:408
msgid "Copper has lower resistance than aluminum"
msgstr "El cobre tiene menor resistencia que el aluminio."

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:409
msgid "Three-phase has lower voltage drop than single-phase"
msgstr "Trifásico tiene menor caída de tensión que monofásico"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:410
msgid "Always follow local electrical codes"
msgstr "Siga siempre los códigos eléctricos locales"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:411
msgid "Consider temperature derating"
msgstr "Considere la reducción de temperatura"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:418
msgid "Electrical circuit design"
msgstr "diseño de circuito electrico"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:419
msgid "Wire sizing for installations"
msgstr "Dimensionado de cables para instalaciones."

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:420
msgid "Troubleshooting voltage issues"
msgstr "Solución de problemas de voltaje"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:421
msgid "Long distance wiring"
msgstr "Cableado de larga distancia"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:422
msgid "Solar panel installations"
msgstr "Instalaciones de paneles solares"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:521
#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:542
msgid "Please enter a valid current"
msgstr "Por favor introduce una corriente válida"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:562
msgid "Please enter a valid voltage drop"
msgstr "Por favor ingrese una caída de voltaje válida"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:582
msgid "Please enter valid values"
msgstr "Por favor introduce valores válidos"

#: Other_Calculators/templates/other_calculators/voltage_drop_calculator.html:621
